#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:1
msgid "Concurrency"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:3
msgid "Establish and enforce a consistent lock order (`lock-ordering`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:5
msgid ""
"Acquiring two locks in different orders from different code paths is a "
"potential deadlock. Hierarchical lock order must be established and "
"documented."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:15
msgid "// Lock order: group of process -> session inner -> job control\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:17
msgid "// ...\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:21
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2942](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2942)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:24
msgid ""
"Never do I/O or blocking operations while holding a spinlock (`no-io-under-"
"spinlock`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:26
msgid ""
"Holding a spinlock while performing I/O or blocking operations is a deadlock "
"hazard. Use a sleeping mutex or restructure to drop the lock first."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:32
msgid "// Good — spinlock dropped before I/O\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:34
#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:40
msgid "// state: SpinLock<...>\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:38
msgid "// Bad — I/O while holding spinlock\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:44
msgid "See also: PR [\\#925](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/925)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:47
msgid "Do not use atomics casually (`careful-atomics`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:49
msgid ""
"When multiple atomic fields must be updated in concert, use a lock. Only use "
"atomics when a single value is genuinely independent."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:55
msgid "// Good — a lock protects correlated fields\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:63
msgid ""
"// Bad — two atomics that must be consistent\n"
"// but can be observed in an inconsistent state\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:72
msgid ""
"Critical sections must not be split across lock boundaries (`atomic-critical-"
"sections`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:74
msgid ""
"Operations that must be atomic (check + conditional action) must happen "
"under the same lock acquisition. Moving a comparison outside the critical "
"region is a correctness bug."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:81
msgid "// Good — check and action under the same lock\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:87
msgid ""
"// Bad — TOCTOU race: state can change\n"
"// between the check and the action\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/concurrency.md:97
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2277](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2277)."
msgstr ""
